review: In the world of restaurants I rate most TGI Fridays as about 3 stars. However, this one way exceeded my expectations. We stopped in here about 10 monutes after happy hour had ended. Luckily, due to our awesome waitress happy hour kept on going for us. Discount appetizers and drinks gave us a feast for kings...I mean queens. We practically rolled ourselves out of the restaurant.
This restaurant is closed and has been for years!  If intentionally horrible service can kill a restaurant, then this restaurant murdered itself.  So bad, so really intentionally bad.

No mas. They packed up and said forget it. Left a sign on door and employees didnt even know about it. Its rough out here I'll tell ya! But yet they keep running tv ads all over the place....... Go figure.
